sql:
SELECT age_group
FROM age_groups
ORDER BY min_age, max_age;

SELECT age_group
FROM age_groups
ORDER BY min_age;

SELECT age_group, ((min_age + max_age) / 2) AS average_age
FROM age_groups
ORDER BY average_age;

external_knowledge:
- The cumulative percentage is calculated by summing up the percentages of each category for the current and all previous age groups; 
- The percentages are calculated relative to the total population, not just the age group; 
- Age groups are ordered by their minimum age for the cumulative calculation.

